#Title#
Dedekind summary
#Content#
Richard Dedekind 1831 - 1916 Richard Dedekind's major contribution was a redefinition of irrational numbers in terms of Dedekind cuts. He introduced the notion of an ideal in Ring Theory. Go to the full MacTutor biography
